  "market_context": "EURUSD in a clear downtrend with lower lows and lower highs; price recently swept liquidity at equal highs (1.07400), then approached an unmitigated order block formed from prior inefficiency.",
  "key_observation": "Price formed an initial bullish candle, a reaction candle, then a bearish engulfing candle breaking below the reaction candle—confirming rejection at the unmitigated order block and signaling short entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the 1H downtrend via series of lower highs and lower lows.",
    "Step 2: Noted price swept the liquidity pool at equal highs (1.07400) marked with '$' symbols.",
    "Step 3: Recognized an unmitigated order block (OB) created by market inefficiency above the recent swing low.",
    "Step 4: Waited for price to reach the OB zone and observed three-candle sequence: initial candle, reaction candle, then bearish engulfing candle breaking below the reaction candle.",
    "Step 5: Confirmed entry after engulfing candle closed, placing stop loss above the highest point of the recent candles (above reaction candle high).",
    "Step 6: Set take profit at either the most recent bullish fair value gap or upcoming sellside liquidity, preferring tighter targets."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A confirmed short entry requires not just proximity to a supply zone but also candlestick confirmation—specifically an engulfing candle breaking key structure—after liquidity sweep and inefficiency identification.",
